00:00:12.843 --> 00:00:16.729
Hi! Welcome to your favorite show, Aha Emi Ruchi!

00:00:26.738 --> 00:00:32.186
What will you be cooking?
Chikoo Peda (Sapodilla Sweet)

00:00:36.476 --> 00:00:38.752
Ingredients required to make Chikoo Peda

00:00:39.127 --> 00:00:45.075
Sapodilla (Chikoo or Sapota), Khova/Khoa (Dried Whole Milk), Gulkand, Powdered Cashews, Almonds

00:01:12.042 --> 00:01:22.821
Add a cup of mashed chikoo/sapota into a hot pan

00:01:24.047 --> 00:01:33.042
Add a cup of khova/khoa and keep mixing them for awhile and then let it cool down

00:02:12.473 --> 00:02:23.930
Meanwhile, take a cup of gulkand (sweet preserve of rose petals)

00:02:31.940 --> 00:02:38.572
Add a cup of powdered cashews to it and mix them

00:02:58.344 --> 00:03:07.449
Roll small balls with this mixture

00:03:41.450 --> 00:04:00.211
Make small puri like flat round pieces with the chikoo/sapota &amp; khova/khoa mixture and
 place the gulkand &amp; cashew balls on the puri and wrap them up and roll them into balls

00:04:12.454 --> 00:04:33.281
Garnish with some almonds and some chikoo/sapota fruits

